Concerns have been raised over a program which allows school students to gain entry to university without completing their final year certificate - and is only being offered to pupils at a prestigious Sydney private school .
The University of Sydney is running a pilot of a 17-week bridging diploma for Year 11 students at the elite school Scot 's College .
The program allows parents to ` buy ' their sons entry to the sandstone university .
The course were reported to be $ 30,900 per year .